                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1165">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 740.6361/6</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé d’Affaires in Russia</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_WCS1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-12T12:00:00+02:30">
                        <hi rend="italic">August 12, 1914, 12 noon</hi>.</date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 13, 12 noon</hi>.] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Department’s August 7, 9 a.m. [August 8, 7 p.m.], and August 9, 8 p.m. Russian
                    Government will not admit that Embassy buildings of Austria-Hungary or Germany
                    enjoy at present any extraterritorial privileges. Foreign Office thinks that
                    raising American flag would only complicate matters and might cause unfortunate
                    incidents. I do not consider building in danger at present. While protesting
                    against molestation of embassies, I shall comply with Foreign Office request
                    unless otherwise instructed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WCS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
